{title: The Last Time I Saw Her Face}
{artist: Glen Campbell}
{composer: Written by Gordon Lightfoot}

[C]The last time [Dm]I saw her face
[G7]Her eyes were bathed in starlight and her [C]hair hung long
The last time [Dm]she spoke to me
[G7]Her lips were like the scented flowers inside a rain-drenched [C]forest
[F]But that was so [G7]long ago that [F]I can scarcely [C]feel
The way I [Dm]felt before  and if [G7]time could [C]heal the wounds
I would tear the [F]threads away that I might [G7]bleed some more
The [C]last time [Dm]I walked with her
[G7]Her laughter was the steeple bells that [F]ring to greet the [G7]morning sun
[F]A voice that called to [G7]everyone [F]to love the ground we [G7]walked upon
